4. Environmental Economics

4.1 Carbon-Negative Transaction Model

4.1.1 Footprint Calculation

```python
def calculate_carbon_footprint(transaction):
    # Compute energy (validators, smart contracts)
    compute_kwh = gas_used × compute_factor
    
    # Network energy (propagation, validation)
    network_kwh = tx_size × network_factor
    
    # Storage energy (blockchain persistence)
    storage_kwh = tx_size × storage_days × storage_factor
    
    # Apply renewable energy discount
    total_kwh = (compute + network + storage) × (1 - renewable_percentage)
    
    # Convert to CO₂e using location-based grid factors
    carbon_kg = total_kwh × grid_emission_factor
    
    return carbon_kg
```

4.1.2 Offset Mechanism

· 150% offset requirement: Each transaction removes 1.5× its carbon footprint
· Verified projects: Direct air capture, reforestation, renewable energy
· Transparent retirement: On-chain verification of credit retirement
· Impact tracking: Real-time dashboard of environmental impact

4.2 Environmental Reserve Assets

