5. Security Architecture

5.1 Quantum Resistance Implementation

5.1.1 Cryptographic Suite

```
Post-Quantum Cryptography Stack:
├── Signatures: Dilithium3 (primary), Falcon-512 (secondary)
├── KEM: Kyber768 (key exchange)
├── Hash: SHA3-256, BLAKE3
└── Hybrid Mode: ECDSA + Dilithium3 for backward compatibility
```

5.1.2 Migration Strategy

1. Phase 1 (2026): Hybrid classical/quantum-resistant system
2. Phase 2 (2027): Quantum-resistant primary with classical fallback
3. Phase 3 (2028): Full quantum resistance, classical deprecation
4. Ongoing: Continuous cryptographic agility for new threats

5.2 Biometric Security

5.2.1 Privacy-Preserving Design

· On-device processing: Biometric matching never leaves user device
· Zero-knowledge proofs: Authentication without revealing biometric data
· Homomorphic encryption: Secure template storage and matching
· Hardware security modules: TPM/HSM integration for key storage

5.2.2 Anti-Spoofing Measures

· Liveness detection: Voice anti-spoofing, fingerprint liveliness
· Multi-modal requirement: Minimum two biometric factors
· Behavioral analytics: Continuous authentication patterns
· Challenge-response: Random authentication challenges

