10. Risk Assessment & Mitigation

10.1 Technical Risks

10.1.1 Quantum Cryptographic Risks

Risk: New quantum attacks or mathematical breakthroughs
Mitigation: Cryptographic agility, hybrid approach, ongoing research partnerships

10.1.2 Smart Contract Risks

Risk: Code vulnerabilities or logic errors
Mitigation: Formal verification, extensive testing, bug bounty programs, insurance coverage

10.2 Financial Risks

10.2.1 Stability Mechanism Risks

Risk: Algorithmic stability failure during extreme volatility
Mitigation: Circuit breakers, over-collateralization, emergency manual intervention

10.2.2 Reserve Risks

Risk: Carbon credit market volatility or verification failures
Mitigation: Diversified reserve composition, multiple verification layers, insurance

10.3 Regulatory Risks

10.3.1 Jurisdictional Risks

Risk: Regulatory bans or restrictive legislation
Mitigation: Multi-jurisdiction strategy, regulatory sandbox participation, proactive engagement

10.3.2 Compliance Risks

Risk: Evolving regulatory requirements
Mitigation: Modular compliance architecture, regulatory monitoring, legal partnerships

10.4 Environmental Risks

10.4.1 Project Risks

Risk: Environmental project failure or underperformance
Mitigation: Diversified project portfolio, performance insurance, satellite monitoring

10.4.2 Verification Risks

Risk: Carbon credit verification fraud
Mitigation: Multiple independent verifiers, blockchain tracking, penalty mechanisms

